<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-01">1 December 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Franklin</persName></hi>, I was indeed touched by your kind
                                    present.<note n="1" xml:id="d402fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_469">p. 469</ref>. According to
                                    Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, <hi rend="italic">The
                                        Tehran Conference</hi>, p. 176, <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> had sent the following signed message
                                    to accompany the bowl: “my affection, may we be together for
                                    many years”.</note> It is a beautiful bowl, and I shall always
                                treasure it as a reminder <pb facs="0736" n="632" xml:id="pg_632"/>
                                of our sunlit days in Tehran and of the most memorable of my
                                Birthdays.</p>
                            <p>I cannot thank you enough for all your friendship and support in the
                                years in which we have worked together, and I am glad of this
                                occasion to send you a message of sincere affection and
                                gratitude.</p>
                            <p>Yours always,</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CWS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Winston
                                            S. Churchill</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>